      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "A note on this - Importing gradle project like you would a maven project does not seem to work. You can&#39;t even say new project from existing sources. The only way to open a gradle project is to have nothing else open, open intellij, and it gives you option to import project. Then import the whole project (not the gradle file), and mark it as a gradle project as this answer describes. I&#39;m about to abandon using intellij because of my constant frustrations with basic things like this. I hate eclipse, but at least it knows what type of project it&#39;s working in."
