      "reputation" : 6348,
      "user_id" : 263690,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 97,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3b83dfe07606310fa9c87fb561c74b90?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "reinaldoluckman",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/263690/reinaldoluckman"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1602544262,
    "creation_date" : 1602544262,
    "answer_id" : 64326465,
    "question_id" : 27694442,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Tried everything in this thread and nothing worked for me in IntelliJ 2020.2. <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/61806948/263690\">This answer did the trick</a>, but I had to set the correct path to the JDK and choose it in Gradle settings after that (as showed in figures bellow):</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Setting the correct path for the Java SDK (under File-&gt;Project Structure):</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/h66TK.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/h66TK.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>In Gradle Window, click in &quot;Gradle Settings...&quot;</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/YymnX.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/YymnX.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Select the correct SDK from (1) here:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4zsSb.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4zsSb.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>After that, the option &quot;Reload All Gradle Projects&quot; downloaded all dependencies as expected.</p>\n<p>Cheers.</p>\n"
  }, {
