    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this exact same error and nothing else worked. Finally, I did the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Close IntelliJ IDEA.</li>\n<li>Delete .idea directory from my project folder.</li>\n<li>Reopen IntelliJ and import the project again (as Gradle).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>After the above, any new gradle dependency I added to build.gradle started appearing in External Dependencies section when I clicked the gradle refresh button.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14677660,
      "reputation" : 288,
      "user_id" : 10600212,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-OXR08q_GNlM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAYA/_iZoB0R3Xbs/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Mang Ndie",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10600212/mang-ndie"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1654565264,
    "creation_date" : 1654565264,
    "answer_id" : 72524992,
    "question_id" : 27694442,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>in my case, just re-import the jar file into correct directory .\nFile-&gt;project Structure-&gt;[Project setting -&gt; Modules]\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/dq0vx.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/dq0vx.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 16517935,
      "reputation" : 896,
      "user_id" : 11934850,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/qcxep.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sascha Doerdelmann",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11934850/sascha-doerdelmann"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1708606832,
    "creation_date" : 1708606832,
    "answer_id" : 78041132,
    "question_id" : 27694442,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case the root project name did not match the root project folder name.</p>\n<p>If I check out some git repository, I typically use snake_case.\nFrom time to time people set a root project name and use a different spelling e.g. CamelCase.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Folder to check out to: my_project</li>\n<li>rootProject.name = 'MyProject'</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Whenever this happened, IntelliJ was not able to calculate the external libraries.</p>\n<p>I deleted the line with the rootProject.name from the gradle.settings file and everything worked fine.</p>\n"
  } ],
